LeacockChodorowComparator - Class in de.tudarmstadt.ukp.similarity.algorithms.lsr.path
Implements the relatedness measure by Leacock and Chodorow (1998) lch(c1,c2) = - log(minPL(c1,c2) / 2 * depth) = log( 2*depth / minPL(c1,c2) ) minPathLength is measured in edges (original definition measures in nodes).

Implements the relatedness measure by Leacock and Chodorow (1998) lch(c1,c2) = - log(minPathLength(c1,c2) / 2 * depth of the hierarchy) lch(c1,c2) = - log(minPL(c1,c2) / 2 * depth) = log( 2*depth / minPL(c1,c2) ) minPathLength is measured in edges (original definition measures in nodes).
